    {
      "section_id": "para_35",
      "heading": "1.  (1)   This Act may be cited as the Innkeepers Act 1952.",
      "content": "1.  (1)   This Act may be cited as the Innkeepers Act 1952.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_36",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)   This Act applies to Peninsular Malaysia only.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_37",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Interpretation",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_38",
      "heading": "2.   In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires—",
      "content": "2.   In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires—",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_39",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "“goods” means any movable property;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_40",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "“inn”  means  any  hotel,  boarding-house  or  other  place  where  any \nperson  is  harboured  or  lodged  for  any  kind  whatsoever  of  hire  or \nreward and where any domestic service whatsoever is rendered by the \nowner, lessee, principal tenant, occupier or manager to the person so \nharboured  or  lodged,  licensed  under  any  written  law  for  the  time \nbeing in force in Peninsular Malaysia;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_41",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "“innkeeper”  means  the  keeper  of  any  such  inn  and  includes  a \ncompany or corporation;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_42",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "“manager” means the agent or servant of the innkeeper for the time \nbeing  in  charge  of  the  inn  or  any  person  duly  appointed  by  the \ninnkeeper to receive the goods of his guests for safe custody;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_43",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "“Peninsular  Malaysia”  has  the  meaning  assigned  thereto  in    \nsection  3  of  the  Interpretation  Acts  1948  and  1967  [Act  388],  and \nincludes the Federal Territory.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_44",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "6                                          Laws of Malaysia                      ACT 248",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_45",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Power of sale of goods deposited with innkeeper",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_46",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "3.   An  innkeeper  shall,  in  addition  to  his  ordinary  lien,  have  the \nright absolutely to sell by public auction any goods which may have \nbeen deposited with him or left in the inn he keeps or in any garage, \ncar  park  or  other  premises  appurtenant  thereto  where  the  person \ndepositing or leaving such goods shall be or become indebted to the \nsaid innkeeper for any board or lodging:",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_47",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Provided that—",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_48",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(a)  no such sale shall be made until after the said goods shall \nhave  been  for  the  space  of  six  weeks  in  such  charge  or \ncustody  or  in  or  upon  such  premises  without  such  debt \nhaving been paid or satisfied;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_49",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(b)  the  innkeeper,  after  having  out  of  the  proceeds  of  such \nsale  paid  himself  the  amount  of  any  such  debt,  together \nwith  the  costs  and  expenses  of  any  such  sale,  shall  on \ndemand pay to the person depositing or leaving any such \ngoods the surplus (if any) remaining after such sale;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_50",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(c)  the debt for the payment of which a sale is made shall not \nbe any other or  greater  debt  than the debt  for which the \ngoods  could  have  been  retained  by  the  innkeeper  under \nhis lien;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_51",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(d)  at  least  one  month  before  any  such  sale  the  innkeeper \nshall  cause  to  be  inserted  in  a  newspaper  circulating  in \nMalaysia  an  advertisement  containing  notice  of  such \nintended  sale,  and  giving  shortly  a  description  of  the \ngoods intended to be sold, together with the name of the \nowner  or  person  who  deposited  or  left  the  same  where \nknown.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_52",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Limitation of innkeepers’ liability",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_53",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "4.   No innkeeper shall be liable to make good to any guest of such \ninnkeeper any loss of or injury to goods brought to his inn, not being \na horse or other live animal, or any gear appertaining thereto or any \ncar  or  carriage,  to  a  greater  amount  than  the  sum  of  five  hundred \nringgit, except in the following cases:",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_54",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Innkeepers                                             7",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_55",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(a)  where such goods shall  have been stolen, lost or injured \nthrough  the  wilful  act,  default  or  neglect  of  such \ninnkeeper or any servant in his employ;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_56",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(b)  where such goods shall have been deposited expressly for",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_57",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "safe custody with such innkeeper or his manager:",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_58",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Provided  always  that  in  the  case  of  such  deposit  it \nshall  be  lawful  for  such  innkeeper  or  his  manager,  if  he \nthinks fit, to require, as a condition of his liability—",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_59",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(i)  that  the  guest  shall  at  the  time  of  such  deposit",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_60",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "declare the value of such goods,",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_61",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(ii)  that such goods shall be deposited in a box or other \nreceptacle,  fastened  and  sealed  by  the  person \ndepositing the same:",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_62",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Provided always that the innkeeper or his manager may refuse to \nreceive for safe custody under this section goods of any one guest the \ndeclared  value  of  which  exceeds  five  thousand  ringgit,  and  that  he \nshall in no case be liable for loss of or injury to goods so deposited by \na guest to an amount exceeding the declared value thereof.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_63",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Refusal to accept property for safe custody",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_64",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "5.  \nIf any innkeeper or his manager shall refuse to receive for safe \ncustody,  as  before  mentioned,  any  goods  of  his  guest  the  declared \nvalue of which does not exceed five thousand ringgit, or if any such \nguest  shall,  through  any  default  of  such  innkeeper  or  manager,  be \nunable to deposit such goods as aforesaid, such innkeeper shall not be \nentitled to the benefit of this Act in respect of such goods.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_65",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Copy of section 4 to be exhibited",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_66",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "6.   Every  innkeeper  shall  cause  at  least  one  copy  of  section  4  of \nthis Act printed in plain type to be exhibited in a conspicuous part of \nthe hall or entrance to his inn, and he shall be entitled to the benefit of \nthis Act in respect of such goods only as shall be brought to his inn \nwhile such copy shall be so exhibited.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_67",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "8                                          Laws of Malaysia                      ACT 248",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_68",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Repeal",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_69",
      "heading": "7.   The Innkeepers’ Liability Ordinance of the Straits Settlements  \n[S.S. Cap. 58] is hereby repealed.",
      "content": "7.   The Innkeepers’ Liability Ordinance of the Straits Settlements  \n[S.S. Cap. 58] is hereby repealed.",
